CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 19, 1946, pg. 15 reads: "Lights Out! - Little Tommy Lee gallantly blows out the candles on his birthday cake as his "heart interest," Erline Palmer, watches with pride. Occasion was Tommy's fifth birthday and his first real "date" with his cute little neighbor.  Tommy is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Charles Lee of 516 Gearing Avenue. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Tommy Lee blowing out birthday candles and Erline Palmer, standing behind table with round cake in home of Mr. and Mrs. Charles Lee, 516 Gearing Avenue
